{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844469583,"sessionID":"ses_2876c0c21ffesOIn7cK5Xz2Hxp","part":{"id":"prt_d78942b13001CA9RgnWs8wrndC","messageID":"msg_d78941479001Bh6oCA3ivCj2IJ","sessionID":"ses_2876c0c21ffesOIn7cK5Xz2Hxp","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-362633c1360c41bfa64aadb8253c8b3f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-005/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-005/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Foundation - Common Types & Constants\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1** Create `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` file\n20:   - Define `CreateSandboxRequest` struct with fields: `Kind`, `Name`, `Namespace`\n21:   - Define `CreateSandboxResponse` struct with fields: `SessionID`, `SandboxID`, `SandboxName`, `EntryPoints`\n22:   - Define `SandboxEntryPoint` struct with fields: `Path`, `Protocol`, `Endpoint`\n23:   - Define `SandboxInfo` struct with fields: `Kind`, `SandboxID`, `SandboxNamespace`, `Name`, `SessionID`, `CreatedAt`, `ExpiresAt`, `Status`, `EntryPoints`, `UserToken`, `ServiceAccount`, `ServiceAccountName`\n24:   - Add JSON tags using camelCase for all fields\n25:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/common/types/...`\n26: \n27: - [ ] **T1.2** Create `pkg/common/types/sandbox_test.go` file\n28:   - Test `CreateSandboxRequest.Validate()` method:\n29:     - Kind must be \"AgentRuntime\" or \"CodeInterpreter\"\n30:     - Namespace must be non-empty\n31:     - Name must be non-empty\n32:     - Return appropriate error messages\n33:   - Test JSON serialization/deserialization for all types\n34:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/common/types/... -v`\n35: \n36: - [ ] **T1.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` file\n37:   - Define constants:\n38:     - `DefaultSandboxTTL = 8 * time.Hour`\n39:     - `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`\n40:     - `DefaultMaxSessionDuration = 8 * time.Hour`\n41:     - `DefaultSessionTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`\n42:     - `SandboxCreationTimeout = 2 * time.Minute`\n43:     - `SandboxDeleteTimeout = 30 * time.Second`\n44:   - Define label/annotation key constants:\n45:     - `LabelKeySessionID = \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\"`\n46:     - `LabelKeyWorkloadName = \"runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name\"`\n47:     - `LabelKeySandboxName = \"runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name\"`\n48:     - `LabelKeyManagedBy = \"managed-by\"`\n49:     - `AnnotationKeyIdleTimeout = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"`\n50:     - `AnnotationKeyPodName = \"agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name\"`\n51:   - Define GVR constants:\n52:     - `SandboxGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxes\"}`\n53:     - `SandboxClaimGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxclaims\"}`\n54:   - Define kind constants:\n55:     - `SandboxKind = \"Sandbox\"`\n56:     - `SandboxClaimKind = \"SandboxClaim\"`\n57:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n58: \n59: - [ ] **T1.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults_test.go` file\n60:   - Test all constant values match design specification\n61:   - Test GVR constants are correctly formed\n62:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestDefaults -v`\n63: \n64: ### Phase 2: K8s Client Infrastructure\n65: \n66: - [ ] **T2.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client.go` file\n67:   - Define `K8sClient` struct with fields:\n68:     - `dynamicClient dynamic.Interface`\n69:     - `informerFactory externalversions.SharedInformerFactory`\n70:     - `agentRuntimeLister listers.AgentRuntimeLister`\n71:     - `codeInterpreterLister listers.CodeInterpreterLister`\n72:     - `podLister corev1listers.PodLister`\n73:     - `coreClient kubernetes.Interface`\n74:   - Define `ClientCache` struct for per-user client caching (if auth enabled)\n75:   - Implement `NewK8sClient(config *rest.Config) (*K8sClient, error)` function\n76:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n77: \n78: - [ ] **T2.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client_test.go` file\n79:   - Test `K8sClient` initialization with fake clientset\n80:   - Test informer factory creation\n81:   - Test lister access methods\n82:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestK8sClient -v`\n83: \n84: - [ ] **T2.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/informers.go` file\n85:   - Define `Informers` struct wrapping `SharedInformerFactory`\n86:   - Implement `NewInformers(k8sClient *K8sClient) *Informers` function\n87:   - Implement `Start(ctx context.Context)` method\n88:   - Implement `WaitForCacheSync(ctx context.Context) bool` method\n89:   - Implement `GetAgentRuntimeInformer() runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeInformer` method\n90:   - Implement `GetCodeInterpreterInformer() runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterInformer` method\n91:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n92: \n93: - [ ] **T2.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/informers_test.go` file\n94:   - Test informer start and stop\n95:   - Test cache sync with timeout\n96:   - Test lister retrieval\n97:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestInformers -v`\n98: \n99: ### Phase 3: Store Integration\n100: \n101: - [ ] **T3.1** Define Store interface in `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n102:   - Add `Store` interface with methods:\n103:     - `StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n104:     - `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n105:     - `UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n106:     - `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error`\n107:     - `ListSandboxes(ctx context.Context) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n108:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n109: \n110: - [ ] **T3.2** Create Store implementation stub (interface only for now)\n111:   - Note: Actual Redis Store implementation is in AR-006 or separate module\n112:   - Create mock Store for testing purposes\n113:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n114: \n115: ### Phase 4: Sandbox Controller & Watcher\n116: \n117: - [ ] **T4.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_controller.go` file\n118:   - Define `SandboxReconciler` struct with fields:\n119:     - `k8sClient *K8sClient`\n120:     - `watchers map[string]chan struct{}`\n121:     - `mutex sync.RWMutex`\n122:   - Implement `WatchSandboxOnce(namespace, name string) (<-chan struct{}, error)` method:\n123:     - Register watcher before CR creation\n124:     - Return channel that closes when sandbox enters \"running\" state\n125:   - Implement `notifyWatcher(namespace, name string)` private method\n126:   - Implement `getSandboxStatus(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) (string, error)` method\n127:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n128: \n129: - [ ] **T4.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_controller_test.go` file\n130:   - Test `WatchSandboxOnce` registration\n131:   - Test watcher channel closes on running status\n132:   - Test concurrent watchers\n133:   - Test watcher cleanup\n134:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestSandboxController -v`\n135: \n136: ### Phase 5: Workload Builder\n137: \n138: - [ ] **T5.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` file\n139:   - Implement `buildSandboxObject(runtime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, sessionID string) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error)`:\n140:     - Generate sandbox name: `{workloadName}-{RandString(8)}`\n141:     - Set APIVersion: `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`\n142:     - Set Kind: `Sandbox`\n143:     - Set labels: session-id, workload-name, sandbox-name, managed-by\n144:     - Set annotations: idle-timeout\n145:     - Set spec.podTemplate from runtime.Spec.Template\n146:     - Set spec.replicas = 1\n147:     - Set spec.lifecycle.shutdownTime = now + MaxSessionDuration\n148:   - Implement `RandString(n int) string` helper for 8-char lowercase random string\n149:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n150: \n151: - [ ] **T5.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder_test.go` file\n152:   - Test `buildSandboxObject` with valid AgentRuntime:\n153:     - Verify name format (workload-8char)\n154:     - Verify labels and annotations\n155:     - Verify podTemplate copied correctly\n156:     - Verify replicas = 1\n157:   - Test `RandString` generates 8 lowercase letters\n158:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestBuildSandboxObject -v`\n159: \n160: - [ ] **T5.3** Implement `buildSandboxClaimObject(ci *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, sessionID string) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error)`:\n161:   - Set APIVersion: `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`\n162:   - Set Kind: `SandboxClaim`\n163:   - Minimal metadata (labels and annotations)\n164:   - No full PodSpec\n165:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n166: \n167: - [ ] **T5.4** Create test for `buildSandboxClaimObject`:\n168:   - Verify correct GVK\n169:   - Verify minimal metadata\n170:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestBuildSandboxClaimObject -v`\n171: \n172: - [ ] **T5.5** Implement `buildCodeInterpreterSandboxObject(ci *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, sessionID string, publicKey []byte) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error)`:\n173:   - Build full Sandbox for WarmPoolSize == 0\n174:   - Single container named \"code-interpreter\"\n175:   - Inject `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var if AuthMode=picod and publicKey available\n176:   - Set default ports if spec.Ports empty: `[{Port: 