ne without public key\n331:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/... -run TestHandleCodeInterpreterCreate -v`\n332: \n333: ### Phase 9: Error Handling & Response Formatting\n334: \n335: - [ ] **T9.1** Implement error mapping in handlers:\n336:   - JSON bind error → 400: `{\"message\":\"Invalid request body\"}`\n337:   - Validation error → 400: `{\"message\":\"<field> is required\"}`\n338:   - Template missing → 400: `{\"message\":\"agent runtime not found: ... pod template missing\"}`\n339:   - Not found → 404: `{\"message\":\"agent runtime not found\"}`\n340:   - Timeout → 500: `{\"message\":\"internal server error\"}`\n341:   - K8s API error → 500: `{\"message\":\"internal server error\"}`\n342:   - Store error → 500: `{\"message\":\"internal server error\"}`\n343:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/...`\n344: \n345: - [ ] **T9.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/response.go` file:\n346:   - Implement `writeJSONResponse(w http.ResponseWriter, status int, data interface{})` helper\n347:   - Implement `writeErrorResponse(w http.ResponseWriter, status int, message string)` helper\n348:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/...`\n349: \n350: - [ ] **T9.3** Create tests for error response formatting:\n351:   - Test each error type produces correct status and JSON\n352:   - Verify Content-Type: application/json header\n353:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/... -run TestErrorResponse -v`\n354: \n355: ### Phase 10: Authentication Middleware\n356: \n357: - [ ] **T10.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/auth.go` file\n358:   - Define context keys:\n359:     - `contextKeyUserToken`\n360:     - `contextKeyServiceAccount`\n361:     - `contextKeyServiceAccountName`\n362:     - `contextKeyNamespace`\n363:   - Implement `authMiddleware(publicKey []byte, enableAuth bool) func(http.Handler) http.Handler`:\n364:     - If EnableAuth=false: pass through\n365:     - If EnableAuth=true:\n366:       - Extract B